 LHASA, Nov. 20 (Xinhua) -- Changtang Plateau has a total lake area of over 25,000 square kilometers. The plateau is located in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region and is known by people for the number and high altitude of lakes. According to statistical data, there are nearly 500 lakes with an area of over one square kilometer and more than 300 lakes with an area of over five square kilometers. Some famous lakes on the plateau include Nam Co Lake, Serling Tso Lake and Zhari Namco Lake, to name a few.  Aerial photo taken on Sept. 23, 2021 shows a lake on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region.(Xinhua/Jigme Dorje)  Aerial photo taken on Sept. 22, 2021 shows a lakeside view on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Purbu Zhaxi)  Photo taken on Sept. 23, 2021 shows a view of a lake on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region.(Xinhua/Purbu Zhaxi)  Aerial photo taken on Sept. 23, 2021 shows a lakeside view of Ombu Township of Nyima County, Nagqu City of southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Purbu Zhaxi)  Photo taken on Sept. 24, 2021 shows Tibetan wild donkeys foraging by a lake on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Jigme Dorje)  Photo taken on Sept. 22, 2021 shows a view of a lake and mountains on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Jigme Dorje)  Aerial photo taken on Sept. 24, 2021 shows a lake on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Sun Ruibo)  Aerial photo taken on Sept. 26, 2021 shows a lake on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Sun Ruibo)  Photo taken on Sept. 22, 2021 shows a view of a lake and mountains on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Jigme Dorje)  Aerial photo taken on Sept. 22, 2021 shows a lake on the Changtang Plateau, in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region. (Xinhua/Purbu Zhaxi)